 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-f0t.3","title":"Config: Move Socket from /tmp to ~/.cache for Persistence","description":"## Problem
The daemon socket is at /tmp/rch.sock which:
1. Gets deleted on system reboot
2. May have permissions issues if multiple users
3. Loses state across reboots

First build after reboot is slow because daemon state is lost.

## Solution
Move socket to user-specific persistent location:
- Linux/macOS: ~/.cache/rch/rch.sock
- Or use XDG_RUNTIME_DIR if available

## Implementation Details
```rust
fn default_socket_path() -> PathBuf {
    // Prefer XDG_RUNTIME_DIR (per-user, survives session)
    if let Ok(runtime_dir) = std::env::var("XDG_RUNTIME_DIR") {
        return PathBuf::from(runtime_dir).join("rch.sock");
    }

    // Fallback to ~/.cache/rch/
    if let Some(cache_dir) = dirs::cache_dir() {
        let rch_cache = cache_dir.join("rch");
        std::fs::create_dir_all(&rch_cache).ok();
        return rch_cache.join("rch.sock");
    }

    // Last resort: /tmp
    PathBuf::from("/tmp/rch.sock")
}
```

## Migration
- Check for existing /tmp/rch.sock
- If daemon running at old location, notify user
- Update all socket_path defaults
- Document location change in release notes

